The Bloemspruit police are appealing for public help in locating a woman (25) who reported a rape case on 13 January 2017, and also the potential witness, Bokang Thapelo Ntholeng. They are wanted to finalise the case, in which a man (25) of Lesotho is the suspect. He is still in police custody. The police believe that Ntholeng could assist in finding the victim, who the suspect allegedly raped at a house in Phase 10, Bloemspruit. Anyone with information about the whereabouts of Ntholeng and the victim is asked to call the investigating officer, Const. Bessie Nthoba, at the Mangaung police station on 061-494-269 or 051-406-4499 during office hours. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  